messages.content:
Step-by-step reasoning:
1. The user wants to make the kitchen cooler if the temperature rises above 78°F.
2. The device is "Ecobee - 276 Kitchen" with ID "n001_t416412733203".
3. We will monitor the Temperature property (COS) and check if it is greater than 78°F.
4. If true, we will lower the Cool Setpoint to a cooler temperature to reduce the temperature.
5. Since the Cool Setpoint range is 32 to 90°F, a reasonable cooler setpoint could be 74°F.
6. The action will be to send the "Cool Setpoint" command with parameter value 74°F.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Cool kitchen when temperature exceeds 78F",
    "condition": {
      ">": {
        "device": "n001_t416412733203",
        "status": "Temperature",
        "value": 78,
        "uom": "fahrenheit",
        "precision": 1
      }
    },
    "action": {
      "device": "n001_t416412733203",
      "command": "Cool Setpoint",
      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "Cool Setpoint",
          "value": 74,
          "uom": "fahrenheit",
          "precision": 1
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
